author: Nick Canizales
title: Football’s Iowa State Contest Scheduled For 11 a.m. Start
text:
Homecoming contest will be televised nationally on ABC, ESPN or ESPN2. Football’s Iowa State Contest Scheduled For 11 a.m. Start Posted: ncanizales@kcentv.com 
WACO, Texas - Baylor football's Homecoming game against Iowa State on Oct. 24 will begin at 11 a.m. CT, the Big 12 office announced Monday. 
Television arrangements for the game to be played at McLane Stadium have not been finalized, but the contest will either air on ABC, ESPN or ESPN2. 
Baylor, ranked a program-best No. 2 in both the AP Top 25 and the Amway Coaches Poll, owns a 5-0 record and a 2-0 mark in Big 12 play. The Bears will host West Virginia in their Big 12 home opener on Saturday before welcoming Iowa State next weekend. 
Baylor currently leads the country in scoring (64.2 ppg) and total offense (725.0 ypg). 
Iowa State is 2-3 on the season and 1-1 in Big 12 play. The Cyclones will host TCU Saturday, before heading to Waco to face the Bears the following week. 
Baylor recorded a 49-28 win against Iowa State last season in Ames. BU leads the all-time series vs. ISU, 7-6, and holds a 4-2 advantage in games played in Waco. 
The game against Iowa State is Baylor’s third on the ESPN family of networks, joining at SMU (ESPN) and vs. Texas Tech (ABC). 
Baylor is 44-43-4 all-time in Homecoming games, but has won its last five. Included in that string of five victories is a 2013 triumph over Iowa State, 71-7. 
At this year's Homecoming game, fans are again asked to "Stripe McLane." Fans can check BaylorBears.com to see what color their section has been designated to wear for Baylor's second Homecoming game on the Brazos River. A special hashtag, #StripeMcLane, has been created for the promotion. 
Tickets to Baylor’s Homecoming contest are sold out. 
To stay current on all things Baylor Football, follow the team on Twitter: @BUFootball. Sports - Latest News More>>
